import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['Body_Mass__g_'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(data['Body_Mass__g_'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['Body_Mass__g_'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Body Mass (g)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of body mass among the penguins?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='Species', y='Beak_Length__mm_', data=data)
    plt.title('How does the beak length vary across different species of penguins?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Species')
    plt.ylabel('Beak Length (mm)')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['Flipper_Length__mm_'], data['Body_Mass__g_'], c=data['Species'].cat.codes, cmap='viridis')
    ax.set_xlabel('Flipper Length (mm)')
    ax.set_ylabel('Body Mass (g)')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between flipper length and body mass?', wrap=True)
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Species")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
